Package opennlp.ccg.util

Interface Summary
Filter<E> Interface for filters that characterize a set by some membership criteria.
TrieMap.KeyExtractor<KeyType> Interface for methods returning an interned key.
 

Class Summary
ArrayListWithIdentityEquals<T> An array list where equality is checked using == on the list elements, which are assumed to be canonical.
CompositeFilter<E> Composes the effects of several filters into a single filter.
DelegatedFilter<E,D> Abstract class for filters that delegates to another filter that tests elements that do not necessarily apply to the same type of elements as this filter.
DisplayPrefs Simple class for holding preferences for converting an object to a string or other displayable representation.
FilteredMap<K,V> A map whose keys must be allowed by a specified key filter.
FilteredSet<E> A set whose elements must be allowed by a specified Filter.
GroupMap<KeyType,ValType> A map where putting a value does not replace an old value but is rather included in a set of values for that key.
Interner<T> A utility class for interning (canonicalizing) objects.
IntHashSetMap A map from ints to sets which allows objects with the same key to be added without overriding previous puts.
InverseFilter<E> A filter that wraps another filter an inverts its effects.
JLineReader A command-line reader based on JLine.
LineReader Abstract command-line reader.
ListMap<KeyType,ValType> A map where putting a value does not replace an old value but is instead included in a list of values for that key.
MembershipFilter<E> A filter that allows elements based on their membership in a set specified at creation.
Pair<TypeA,TypeB> Dinky class to package pairs of things.
SingletonList<T> An unmodifiable list of one element.
StructureSharingList<T> An unmodifiable list formed by sequencing two sublists.
TrieMap<KeyType,DataType> Implements a trie with a data object at each node.
VisitedFilter<E> A filter that tracks which elements have already been visited by some process or iteration, allowing only those that have not yet been visited.
Visualizer Class for visualizing CCG derivations using latex.
XmlScanner Quick-and-dirty class for using JDOM elements in parsing XML without building a document for the whole XML file.
XmlScanner.MyScanner Example scanner: prints root, counts top- and second-level elements.
